# Troubleshooting

## Issue: VLAN 99 not appearing on trunk

### Symptoms

```text
Vlans allowed and active in management domain
10,20,30
```

### Resolution

Created VLAN 99 on both switches and added it to the trunk:

```cisco
switchport trunk allowed vlan add 99
```

---

## Issue: Incorrect Trunk Command Syntax

### Attempted Command

```cisco
switchport mode trunk vlan 99
```

### Error

```text
Invalid input detected at '^' marker.
```

### Resolution

Used the correct command:

```cisco
switchport trunk allowed vlan add 99
```

---

## Issue: Ambiguous IOS Commands

### Example

```cisco
show int tr
```

### Error

```text
% Ambiguous command
```

### Resolution

Use the full command:

```cisco
show interfaces trunk
```

---

## Lessons Learned

- VLANs must exist locally on each switch to be active across a trunk.
- Allowed VLANs and active VLANs are different concepts.
- Trunk ports carry traffic for multiple VLANs using 802.1Q tagging.
- Verification commands are just as important as configuration commands.
- Layer 2 switches forward traffic within the same VLAN only.
- Inter-VLAN routing requires a router or Layer 3 switch.
